name: Hamming Distance
description:
Hamming distance between two strings of equal length is the number of
positions at which the corresponding symbols are different. You are given two
strings; calculate the distance between them. Input The input consists of two
lines. Each line contains a string of characters 'A'-'Z' between 1 and 100
characters, inclusive. The strings have equal length. Output Output Hamming
distance between the strings. Examples Input CODECHEF TOPCODER Output 6 Input
HAMMING DISTANC Output 6
